Privacy Policy for the “TV Control with Smart Speakers” Application
Last Updated and Effective Date: August 5, 2024
This privacy policy (“Privacy Policy”) applies to the “TV Control with Smart Speakers” Application (the “Application”). The Application is an application to enable a compatible voice-control device to control your TV. In this Privacy Policy, when we say “Sony”, “we”, “us” and “our”, we mean Sony Corporation with an address of 1-7-1 Konan, Minato-ku, Tokyo 108-0075, Japan. Sony acts as data controller (as this term is defined under the General Data Protection Regulation (
(EU) 2016/679
) or any other applicable local legislation or regulation) and may collect and consolidate certain information about you, this Application and/or your TV. This is explained in detail in this Privacy Policy.
In this Privacy Policy, “Sony group companies” shall mean Sony Group Corporation and any legal entities controlled by Sony Group Corporation (the term “control” in this context means the direct or indirect ownership of at least fifty percent (50%) of the voting interest in such corporation or the power in fact to control the management decisions of such entity).
This Privacy Policy only applies to the Application and is in addition to any other privacy policy that may apply to your interactions with any Sony group company or any third party, regarding their product, software or service.
PLEASE NOTE: In order to use this Application, you will need to set up a Sony account (Sony’s Cloud Service for Home Entertainment & Sound Products) which has a separate privacy policy. The voice-control device that is compatible with your TV will depend upon the TV model.
