2. What Collected Data does Sony obtain about you?
Sony may receive the following data that you provide and that is collected automatically from your TV or third parties when you use this Application (the “Collected Data”). Some of the Collected Data may be considered personal information under applicable law in your jurisdiction.
(i)
Collected from you
TV name (that you have entered yourself into the Application)
(ii)
Collected by Sony’s cloud service for Home Entertainment & Sound Products (“Sony’s cloud service”) from your TV
TV information (such as model name, software version, locale, the name of the function which responses to the voice command)
Data regarding how your TV responded to voice commands (such the result of the voice command, the name of application that responded to the voice command)
The state of your TV (such as power state, play back state, volume of sound, use of each channel and external input)
IP address and approximate location inferred from IP address
(iii)
Issued by Sony’s cloud service server
UUID issued by Sony’s cloud service
Access token of Sony’s cloud service
Authorization code of Sony’s cloud service
(iv)
Collected from 3rd parties
Token of “Firebase Cloud Message”
Voice command
The UUID issued by Sony’s cloud service is a unique number assigned to your Application in order to send Voice command from compatible voice-control devices to your BRAVIA.  The Access token and Authorization Code for Sony’s cloud service are issued to your Application as a result of the authentication by Sony’s cloud service.
3. How does Sony use the Collected Data?
(i) To provide you with the services you have requested
Sony uses the Collected Data to process your request, via a compatible voice-control device, to do things like turning on/off your TV, channel switching, volume control and turning on/off installed application. Upon receiving your request, Sony processes the voice commend for your TV and sends back a response from your TV to your compatible voice control device.
It is necessary for Sony to use this Collected Data to provide you with these services.
Please note that the legal basis under EU law for this processing is Article 6 (1) (b) General Data Protection Regulation, the necessity of performing our obligations in connection with the end user license agreement Sony has with you for your use of the Application.
(ii) Security
Sony also processes the Collected Data where it is necessary to ensure information security.
Please note that the legal basis under EU law for this processing is Article 6 (1) (f) General Data Protection Regulation, the necessity for the purposes of the legitimate interests pursued by the controller or by a third party.
(iii) Required by Law
Collected Data may be processed if mandated by law.
Please note that the legal basis under EU law for this processing is Article 6 (1) (c) General Data Protection Regulation, the necessity for compliance with a legal obligation.
4. Who else has access to the Collected Data?
The Collected Data that is communicated to and stored by Sony will be made available to Amazon, if you choose to use compatible voice control device, in order to provide you with this service, and to other Sony group companies and third party service providers, as follows:
(i) Amazon
To link your TV and the Amazon Alexa compatible device via this Application, Sony will share the following Collected Data with Amazon:
 TV name (that you have entered yourself into the Application)
 The state of your TV (such as power state, play back state, volume of sound, use of each channel and external input)
 Amazon Access token
 UUID issued by Sony’s cloud service
 Access token of Sony’s cloud service
 Authorization code of Sony’s cloud service
For more information, please see Amazon’s Website (
https://www.amazon.com/gp/help/customer/display.html?nodeId=201809740
), which also explains where and how such Collected Data collected by Amazon can be deleted.
(ii) Sony group companies
The Collected Data will be sent and stored in Sony’s server which is managed by Sony Electronics Inc., established in the United States, for the purposes of pursuing the activities outlined in Sections 3 (How does Sony use the Collected Data?) above. Sony has implemented appropriate safeguards to ensure these data transfers are made in compliance with applicable local laws.
If you contact your local Sony group companies in relation to questions about the Application, Sony may need to share the Collected Data with that Sony group companies to assist with your request.　Sony may otherwise share Collected Data with Sony group companies for other purposes set out in this Privacy Policy.
(iii) Service Providers
Sony may use third party service providers to store and process the Collected Data on their behalf for the purposes set out in this Privacy Policy. Such third parties include, but are not limited to, IT service providers and data hosting providers.
(iv) Business transfer
In the event that Sony sells or transfers a portion or all of its business, the Collected Data may be transferred by Sony to the purchasing or acquiring entity as part of the transaction, including any due diligence process connected to the sale or transfer. Sony will continue to ensure the confidentiality of the Collected Data before such transaction occurs, and after such transaction, Sony will delete the Collected Data as soon as reasonably practicable after such transaction.
(v) Government Authorities / Law Enforcement Officials
The Collected Data may be disclosed to government authorities and/or law enforcement officials if required by the applicable laws.
(vi) Other Unaffiliated Third Parties
Sony may disclose Collected Data to auditors or similar external consultants like lawyers or tax advisors, to defend and exercise our legal rights (e.g. enforcing compliance with the terms of use) and as Sony believes necessary to comply with our legal obligations.
5. Data Retention, Managing the Collected Data
Sony will retain the Collected Data described in Section 2 for approximately 6 months after your last access to this Application and the compatible voice-control device application.  If you would like to delete the Collected Data collected via this Application or if you would like to withdraw your consent, you can go to [Home] > [TV Control with Smart Speakers] > [Settings] > [Privacy Policy], at any time. Alternatively, please contact us at the address set out below and Sony will respond in a reasonable time. After you withdraw your consent, Sony will stop using the Collected Data, and the Collected Data will be deleted automatically after 6 months.  Please note that Sony may be required to retain certain Collected Data by law. Where Sony no longer requires the Collected Data, it will be destroyed or de-identified in line with our internal information security policies.
6. Transfer of the Collected Data internationally
The Collected Data will be processed, stored and transferred for the purposes outlined in Sections 3 (How does Sony use the Collected Data?) from your country of residence to Japan, EU (Ireland) and the United States. The Collected Data will be processed by staff operating outside your country of residence who work for us or for one of our service providers and may be seen by such staff in those countries. By using the Application, or providing us with any information, you fully understand and consent to this transfer, processing and storage of your information in the United States, Japan and other jurisdictions, where the privacy laws may not be as comprehensive as those in the country where you reside and/or are a citizen. Courts, law enforcement, and other authorities in countries/regions outside your residence may be entitled to access Collected Data upon its transfer.
[For residents in EEA and UK]
Sony takes appropriate measures to ensure that all transfers of Collected Data to outside of the EEA/the UK meet the requirements of applicable EU and UK data protection legislation. As the Collected Data will be transferred to and processed in countries outside the EEA and the UK, where the privacy laws may not provide an equivalent level of protection to those in your home country, and where this is to a stakeholder or vendor in a country that is not subject to an adequacy decision by the European Commission or the UK Government, the Collected Data is adequately protected by Standard Contractual Clauses approved by the European Commission which can be accessed at https://commission.europa.eu/publications/standard-contractual-clauses-international-transfers_en, the addendum to the EU Commission’s standard contractual clauses or standalone international data transfer agreement approved under the UK data protection law (as applicable) or a stakeholder’s/vendor’s Processor Binding Corporate Rules. If you have questions or concerns about Sony's data transfer arrangements, or if you require a copy of the relevant mechanism, please contact us as described in
Section 12. Contact Us
below.
7. Security
Sony establishes a common policy, which are built upon industry standards and best practices like the International Organization for Standardization (ISO) 27001 family of standards and National Institute of Standards and Technology (NIST) standards and adopts strict security control measures for personal data collected and possessed by Sony. These measures include implementation and periodical review of organizational information security management system, periodical training and awareness program, periodical inventory of information assets, physical security control measures (employee access control, client control, etc.), encrypted communications, strict access control, periodical vulnerability assessment of information systems, etc.
Whenever Sony uses service providers (including subcontractors) to process the personal data, Sony confirms that such service providers (including subcontractors) have adopted the necessary and appropriate security control measures. In addition, Sony also expresses its basic policy on handling of personal information in the “Sony Group Japan - Common Corporate Privacy Policy” (https://www.sony.co.jp/privacy-policy/). Please refer to such policy as well for an overview of security control measures.
8. Our Policy Regarding Children
Sony is committed to complying with all applicable laws and regulations regarding the collection, storage and use of personal information concerning children, including the Children's Online Privacy Protection Act in the United States and applicable local legislation in other countries.
This Application is intended for a general audience; the Application is not directed to and does not knowingly collect personal information from children under the age of 16. Depending on your country/region of residence, this threshold age for a child may differ.
If you are a parent or guardian and are concerned that your child has provided Sony with personal data/ personally identifiable information (as defined by applicable law) without your consent, you should contact us at the address set forth as indicated below.
